
  1. pkg build → computes entrypoint_checksum (binary SHA256) → stores in manifest  ✅
  2. pkg publish → uploads manifest with entrypoint_checksum to repository           ✅
  3. ResolveByEntrypointChecksum RPC → node-agent queries: "which version has this binary?"  ✅
  4. Node-agent heartbeat → confirms version from repository, writes to etcd          ✅

  All steps implemented:
  - Proto regenerated with ResolveByEntrypointChecksum RPC stubs
  - Repository server handler scans published manifests for matching entrypoint_checksum
  - Repository client exposes ResolveByEntrypointChecksum() method
  - packageManifest struct enriches entrypoint_checksum from package.json into ArtifactManifest
  - Node-agent heartbeat Phase 3 calls ResolveByEntrypointChecksum when binary doesn't match etcd
  - Lazy repo connection (only connects if a mismatch is found)
  - Falls back gracefully to etcd version if repository lookup fails
